headline: ONEOK (NYSE:OKE) Reports Q1 2025 Revenue Surge to US$8 Billion
summary: ONEOK (NYSE:OKE) recently released its first-quarter earnings, reporting revenue of USD 8,043 million, a marked increase year-over-year, but a minor dip in net income and earnings per share. Alongside this, the company reaffirmed its quarterly dividend of $1.03 per share. These updates coincide with a 4.5% price increase over the week, which aligns with broader market gains of 5.2%. Despite fluctuations in major indices due to economic data and earnings reports from numerous companies,...
